{"fsPath":"/home/khanh/src/0_github/leetcode/prep/vulcan/01_system_design/SYS-chat-messaging/impl/CODEBASE_BREAKDOWN.md","fileUuid":"6c24103f-d525-4a0e-b3d5-83b05db4fc68","fileSizeBytes":6235,"numLines":215,"diffChanges":[{"originalStartLineNumberOneIndexed":1,"originalEndLineNumberExclusiveOneIndexed":1,"modifiedStartLineNumberOneIndexed":1,"modifiedEndLineNumberExclusiveOneIndexed":216,"addedLines":["# CODEBASE BREAKDOWN","","This document explains exactly how the current `impl` codebase is structured, what each file does, and how requests flow through the system.","","## 1) High-level architecture","","The implementation is split into 4 runnable binaries:","","- `migrate`: applies schema to PostgreSQL.","- `api`: REST endpoints for read/query operations.","- `gateway`: WebSocket entrypoint for realtime client events.","- `worker`: background outbox publisher (Postgres -> Redis Streams).","","Shared logic lives under `internal/`:","","- `config`: environment-based config loader and validation.","- `db`: DB/Redis connectors and schema bootstrap.","- `core`: domain/business logic (message create, ack delivery, ack read).","- `transport`: HTTP/WS protocol handlers that call `core`.","- `worker`: outbox polling/publish loop.","","## 2) Folder-by-folder map","","### `cmd/`","","- `cmd/migrate/main.go`","  - Loads config.","  - Connects to Postgres.","  - Runs `db.EnsureSchema`.","","- `cmd/api/main.go`","  - Loads config and Postgres.","  - Builds `core.Service`.","  - Serves:","    - `GET /healthz`","    - `GET /messages`","    - `POST /read`","","- `cmd/gateway/main.go`","  - Loads config and Postgres.","  - Builds `core.Service` + WS handler.","  - Serves:","    - `GET /healthz`","    - `GET /ws`","","- `cmd/worker/main.go`","  - Loads config.","  - Connects to Postgres + Redis.","  - Starts outbox polling loop with graceful shutdown on SIGINT/SIGTERM.","","### `internal/config/`","","- `internal/config/config.go`","  - Defines `Config` struct.","  - Loads env vars with defaults (`POSTGRES_URL`, `REDIS_ADDR`, `HTTP_ADDR`, etc.).","  - Validates:","    - `OUTBOX_BATCH_SIZE > 0`","    - `PRESENCE_TTL > HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL`","","### `internal/db/`","","- `internal/db/postgres.go`","  - `ConnectPostgres`: creates `pgxpool`, pings DB.","","- `internal/db/redis.go`","  - `ConnectRedis`: creates Redis client, pings Redis.","","- `internal/db/schema.go`","  - `EnsureSchema`: executes DDL statements for all tables/indexes.","  - Tables:","    - `users`","    - `conversations`","    - `members`","    - `conversation_sequences`","    - `messages`","    - `message_receipts`","    - `outbox_events`","","### `internal/core/`","","- `internal/core/types.go`","  - Domain DTOs:","    - `Message`","    - `CreateMessageInput`","    - `DeliveryAckInput/Result`","    - `ReadAckInput/Result`","","- `internal/core/service.go`","  - Main business logic with PostgreSQL transactions.","  - `CreateMessage`:","    - checks submit idempotency (`sender_id + client_message_id`)","    - allocates per-conversation sequence","    - inserts into `messages`","    - writes `message.created` into `outbox_events`","  - `RecordDeliveryAck`:","    - inserts `delivered` receipt idempotently","    - writes `message.delivery_ack` outbox event","  - `RecordReadAck`:","    - validates message belongs to conversation","    - updates read pointer monotonically (`last_read_message_id` only advances)","    - inserts `read` receipt idempotently","    - writes `message.read_ack` outbox event","  - `ListMessages` and `MarkRead` helper APIs.","","- `internal/core/service_test.go`","  - Unit tests for helper semantics:","    - dedup detection","    - monotonic read-pointer advance logic","","### `internal/transport/`","","- `internal/transport/ws.go`","  - WebSocket protocol adapter.","  - Parses `user_id` and optional `device_id` from query params.","  - Handles events:","    - `heartbeat` -> `heartbeat_ack`","    - `send_message` -> `server_ack`","    - `ack_delivery` -> `delivery_ack_ok`","    - `ack_read` -> `read_ack_ok`","  - On invalid payload/event, returns `error` envelope.","","- `internal/transport/api.go`","  - REST protocol adapter.","  - `GET /messages` calls `core.ListMessages`.","  - `POST /read` calls `core.MarkRead` (which delegates to `RecordReadAck`).","","### `internal/worker/`","","- `internal/worker/outbox.go`","  - Polls `outbox_events` rows with `status='pending'`.","  - Publishes each row to Redis Stream `chat.conv.{aggregate_id}`.","  - Marks row `published` on success.","  - Increments `retry_count` if publish fails.","","## 3) Infra + developer tooling","","- `docker-compose.yml`","  - Starts `postgres:16` and `redis:7`.","  - Includes health checks and Postgres volume.","","- `Makefile`","  - Common commands:","    - `make infra-up`","    - `make migrate`","    - `make run-worker`","    - `make run-api`","    - `make run-gateway`","    - `make test`","    - `make build`","","- `.env.example`","  - Documents environment knobs and defaults.","","- `migrations/001_init.sql`","  - SQL mirror of programmatic schema in `internal/db/schema.go`.","","- `bench/k6/smoke.js`","  - minimal `healthz` smoke check via k6.","","## 4) Runtime data flow (current implementation)","","### Send message flow","","1. Client sends `send_message` to `gateway` WS.","2. `gateway` calls `core.CreateMessage`.","3. `core` transaction writes `messages` + `outbox_events(message.created)`.","4. `gateway` replies with `server_ack`.","5. `worker` later publishes outbox row to Redis Stream.","","### Delivery ack flow","","1. Client sends `ack_delivery`.","2. `gateway` calls `core.RecordDeliveryAck`.","3. `core` inserts `message_receipts` (`delivered`) idempotently.","4. `core` writes `outbox_events(message.delivery_ack)`.","5. `gateway` replies with `delivery_ack_ok`.","","### Read ack flow","","1. Client sends `ack_read`.","2. `gateway` calls `core.RecordReadAck`.","3. `core` validates message ownership in conversation.","4. `core` advances `members.last_read_message_id` only if seq increases.","5. `core` inserts `message_receipts` (`read`) idempotently.","6. `core` writes `outbox_events(message.read_ack)`.","7. `gateway` replies with `read_ack_ok`.","","## 5) Current boundaries and known gaps","","Implemented:","","- transactional message write with outbox","- idempotent submit and ack persistence","- monotonic read pointer update","- outbox -> Redis Streams publisher","","Not yet implemented (planned next):","","- stream consumer fanout to recipient gateways (Phase 4)","- presence/session registry and reconnect replay (Phase 4)","- stronger authz/rate limit hardening (later phase)","- deep integration tests with real Postgres/Redis for ack/outbox end-to-end","","## 6) Where to start reading as a developer","","Recommended reading order:","","1. `cmd/gateway/main.go`","2. `internal/transport/ws.go`","3. `internal/core/service.go`","4. `internal/worker/outbox.go`","5. `internal/db/schema.go`","","This sequence gives you request entrypoint -> domain logic -> async publish -> persistence model.",""],"tokenizedAddedLines":[1000000,1000001,1000002,1000001,1000003,1000001,1000004,1000001,1000005,1000006,1000007,1000008,1000001,1000009,1000001,1000010,1000011,1000012,1000013,1000014,1000001,1000015,1000001,1000016,1000001,1000017,1000018,1000019,1000020,1000001,1000021,1000022,1000023,1000024,1000025,1000026,1000027,1000001,1000028,1000022,1000029,1000024,1000025,1000030,1000001,1000031,1000018,1000032,1000033,1000001,1000034,1000001,1000035,1000036,1000037,1000038,1000039,1000040,1000001,1000041,1000001,1000042,1000043,1000001,1000044,1000045,1000001,1000046,1000047,1000048,1000049,1000050,1000051,1000052,1000053,1000054,1000055,1000001,1000056,1000001,1000057,1000058,1000059,1000060,1000061,1000062,1000001,1000063,1000064,1000065,1000066,1000067,1000068,1000069,1000070,1000071,1000072,1000073,1000074,1000075,1000076,1000077,1000078,1000001,1000079,1000080,1000081,1000082,1000001,1000083,1000001,1000084,1000085,1